Properties of α-cut

∪(αAi) ⊆ (∪Ai)α and ∩(αAi) = (∩Ai)α;

∪(α+Ai) = (∪Ai)α+ and ∩(α+Ai) ⊆ (∩Ai)α+.

A ⊆ B iff αA ⊆ αB;
A ⊆ B iff α+A ⊆ α+B;
A = B iff αA = αB;
A = B iff α+A = α+B.

αA = ∩(β<α) βA = ∩(β<α) β+A;
α+A = ∪(α<β) βA = ∪(α<β) β+A.

Properties of extension principle

f(A) = ∅ iff A = ∅;
if A₁ ⊆ A₂, then f(A₁) ⊆ f(A₂);
f(∪ Aᵢ) = ∪ f(Aᵢ);
f(∩ Aᵢ) ⊆ ∩ f(Aᵢ);
if B₁ ⊆ B₂, then f⁻¹(B₁) ⊆ f⁻¹(B₂);
f⁻¹(∪ Bᵢ) = ∪ f⁻¹(Bᵢ);
f⁻¹(∩ Bᵢ) = ∩ f⁻¹(Bᵢ);
f⁻¹(B̅) = f⁻¹(B)̅;
A ⊆ f⁻¹(f(A));
B ⊇ f(f⁻¹(B)).
